name: Dulles Town Center
directions: There are multiple gender neutral/family restrooms in this mall, as far as I know! The one I always use is on the ground level. If you park outside of The Cheesecake Factory & PF Chang’s, keep walking to the right of the main doors that you’ll be facing (outside the mall) and you’ll hit an entrance right before the bathrooms (gendered multiple stall, and gender neutral single stall). The entrance I’m referring to is below a place called Sheffield Furniture & Interiors. There’s a sign for it right above the doors that you need to walk through!
comment: Not always a clean bathroom, but it’s been safe (in my experience). It’s tucked away in a corner, and it’s single stall! It’s accessible, has a changing table, short sink, and higher sink. I think it also has a mini urinal, but I’m not sure. If you’re inside the mall, you can find this bathroom right past Hollister. When you pass Hollister’s entrance on your right, take a right at that corner, walk down, then take another right at the end of the hallway. If you’re coming from Forever 21, go down the escalators (outside of Old Navy) take a left when you get down, past the escalators, and you’ll see the restrooms after passing Jos. A. Bank

name: Chipotle
directions: When you walk through the main doors, turn right immediately and you’ll see both single-stall gendered restrooms
comment: I’ve never had an issue here, but maybe be a little extra careful just because the bathrooms are in full view of the food line— people can unfortunately plainly see which bathroom you’re going in to. I think you can use these bathrooms and not be a customer. They’re usually fairly clean!

name: Starbucks

comment: As far as I remember, there are no changing tables. It’s been a safe place for me, regardless of the fact that the bathrooms are technically gendered. I believe they’re accessible! I don’t think you need to be a customer to use these restrooms, but I’m not 100% sure about that
